caption: The image depicts a simplified representation of a bar magnet with its north (N) and south (S) poles indicated at opposite ends. The magnet is outlined with a light blue border, and there are lines between the N and S labels suggesting the magnetic field lines running from the north pole to the south pole. The interior of the magnet is left blank, emphasizing the poles and the concept of magnetic orientation.
scientific_context: This diagram is commonly used in physics to illustrate the basic properties of magnets and the direction of magnetic fields. It helps in understanding fundamental concepts such as magnetic polarity and the behavior of magnetic fields.
